    "rationale": [
      "Apple SpeechTranscriber is the first vertical-slice backend because it combines 7.58% macro WER with the lowest warm latency and process RSS, real incremental results, and word timestamps.",
      "Whisper large-v3-turbo remains the opt-in proven quality and coverage fallback; its 2.90 GB model, 2.00 GB peak RSS, 774 ms warm latency, and batch-only output make it a poor default.",
      "Parakeet remains a compatibility baseline because it is less accurate than Apple SpeechTranscriber on this matrix without adding streaming or a smaller materialized model.",
      "Direct official MLX remains a first-class research foundation; Whisper Tiny proves the boundary but its multilingual quality is not sufficient for product selection.",
      "Qwen3-ASR 0.6B and Voxtral Realtime are reference-oracle research candidates, not accepted product dependencies; both require repository-owned official-MLX boundaries and held-out target-domain evidence.",
      "Voxtral Realtime at 2,400 ms has the lowest raw macro WER in this ten-clip matrix, but neither Voxtral run measured incremental audio input, and both are much slower and heavier than the selected product paths."
    ]
  },
  "limitations": [
    "Two fixtures per language expose language-path failures but are not statistically sufficient for a final quality ranking.",
    "The Qwen reference reports token emissions after whole-clip preprocessing, and the Voxtral reference runs load complete clips; neither is live-input streaming evidence.",
    "Energy was not measured because the documented powermetrics procedure requires privileged, alternating runs.",
    "Cold-load measurements use warm system and model caches and are not clean-host startup measurements.",
    "Candidate order was not alternated, so thermal and background-load effects were not controlled."
